{
  "texts": [
    "The credibility of scientific research is defined by ethical considerations, peer evaluation, and reproducibility (Prager et al., 2019).",
    "However, negligence in critically evaluating genAI produced research risks eroding these fundamental principles.",
    "Therefore, to ensure research integrity, transparency, and mitigate overreliance on automated results, it is essential to establish and integrate genAI usage policies in academia (Athaluri et al., 2023).",
    "Prominent journals warns of a global \"feedback loop\" that risks reinforcing pre-existing knowledge patterns at the expense of transformative inquiry if genAI tools remain unmonitored (Kwong et al., 2024).",
    "Furthermore, a recent analysis elucidates that true intelligence is characterized by the ability to solve novel, previously un-encountered problems, rather than relying on recycling pre-existing solutions (Gignac and Szodorai, 2024)."
  ]
}